arch:property.oc:show_val: Dry sift: A small unit, moderately weathered and looking rather kicked around. Mostly 003, but with some 007 animals. Some low temperature burning, minimal digestion. Sheep-size and large mammal, looks like range of body parts, mostly long bones. Completed: sample 2, flot no. 3281, >4mm, 100%. Lots of little burned bits. Perhaps 75-80% burnt, much of it at high temperatures. Fragmented by burning, though pieces up to 5-6 cm in unit. Sample 2, flot#3329 was recorded for diagnostics only. Last number = 136

arch:string.div: The unique identifier for each contextual unit, matching those used in the central Çatalhöyük excavation database and in publications. The excavation uses single-context recording.
